{
  "texts": [
    "As SHAP has also demonstrated proficiency in time-series analysis (Alsuradi, Park, & Eid, 2020; Theissler, Spinnato, Schlegel, & Guidotti, 2022) it provides a methodologically sound approach capable of navigating the complexities inherent to the data at hand.",
    "Most importantly, our study requires post hoc explanations that provide global insights into feature importance.",
    "SHAP's ability to provide a comprehensive view of critical features in time series data intuitively interpretable for experimental psychologists and neuroscientists makes it a good fit for an application in this field.",
    "While there has been a considerable amount of research conducted in the field of machine learning for EEG data analysis in various applications, foremost in the area of braincomputer interface (BCI), ERP detection remains a niche area of research.",
    "Despite this, several relevant studies have been conducted in this area."
  ]
}